      <akn:section eId="sec_4_1410">
        <akn:num>4-1410</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Authority to charge or receive compensation for services; inability to pay adoption costs.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1410_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1410_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1410_b_1">
      <akn:num>(b-1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In addition to the fee set forth in subsection (b) of this section, a child-placing agency providing domestic or international adoption services that is authorized to charge a fee pursuant to subsection (a) of this section may charge an adoptive parent reasonable fees, but not more than the actual cost, for the following:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1410_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except for a reasonable, nonrefundable administrative fee, a child-placing agency shall not retain the fee paid by an adoptive parent unless the child-placing agency has provided the service.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-1410_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
